a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. ClickUp AI is best suited for project managers, agencies, growing teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Todoist, meanwhile, shines for individuals, freelancers, GTD practitioners, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, ClickUp AI describes itself as \"All-in-one productivity platform with role-based AI writing and task management.\" Todoist, established in 2007, positions itself as \"Simple and powerful task manager with natural language input and smart scheduling.\" With 10 years between them, Todoist brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while ClickUp AI offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **ClickUp AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (10 vs 8), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Todoist is a poor choice — far from it. Todoist excels in its own right, particularly for individuals and freelancers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value extremely feature-rich platform, go with ClickUp AI. If best natural language task input matters more to you, Todoist is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
